  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nAs suggested by @jmcruz1983 [here](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/issues/3613#issuecomment-1545530292) we should update the `/eth/v1/node/health` endpoint to account for the execution node's sync status.\r\n\r\nI think we should change the semantics to return syncing if:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlet unhealthy = syncing || el_offline || optimistic\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently it's just checking the BN's sync status.\r\n\r\n## Additional Info\r\n\r\nRelated to #4291, which will add the `el_offline` field.\r\n",
